<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="noise-n">noise <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /nɔɪz/    美 /nɔɪz/  </p>
<p>[C] &amp; [U]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(令人不快的) 声音；噪音：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t <strong>make</strong> so much <strong>noise</strong>. 
别吵吵嚷嚷。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I covered my ears, trying to keep the noises out, but failed.
我捂上耳朵尽力阻止噪音，但这并不起作用。</p></div>

<h3 id="noise-sound-voice">辨析 noise, sound, voice</h3>
<p><strong>noise ** 通常指不悦耳的、令人烦恼的嘈杂声，隐含贬义。
</strong>sound ** 是普通用词，含义笼统，指人们能听到的各种声音，无褒贬色彩。
**voice ** 指人说话或唱歌时发出的声音。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You’ll have to <strong>raise your voice</strong> if you want to be heard in here. 
在这里，如果想让别人听见你说话，你必须大点儿声。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I could hear angry voices in the next room. 
我能听到隔壁房间的怒吼声。</p></div></div>